	(4,NULL,1,2,1,'Episode 002: Camping','episode-002-camping','','Chris Van Pelt discussing Camping, a microframework built by Why the Lucky Stiff. Chris also gives us a preview of a cool little Camping app he built title Croppr.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_002.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/002_camping.m4v',NULL,'<p>Chris Van Pelt discussing Camping, a microframework built by Why the Lucky Stiff. Chris also gives us a preview of a cool little Camping app he built title Croppr.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/002_camping.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_002.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-07-24 20:41:05','2006-07-24 20:41:07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,NULL),
	(5,NULL,1,3,1,'Episode 003: mkmf','episode-003-mkmf','','Kevin Clark takes us through some of the work he\'s doing on mkmf for his Summer of Rails project. We also get a quick preview of Kevin\'s RailsDay app, Advisr.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_003.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/003_mkmf.m4v',NULL,'<p>Kevin Clark takes us through some of the work he&#8217;s doing on mkmf for his Summer of Rails project. We also get a quick preview of Kevin&#8217;s RailsDay app, Advisr.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/003_mkmf.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_003.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-07-24 20:50:19','2006-07-24 20:50:19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,NULL),
	(6,NULL,1,4,1,'Episode 004: Numbers','episode-004-numbers','','Tom Werner wows us with the power of numbers in Ruby.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_004.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/004_numbers.m4v',NULL,'<p>Tom Werner wows us with the power of numbers in Ruby.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/004_numbers.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_004.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-09-08 17:11:15','2006-09-08 17:11:16',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,NULL),
	(7,NULL,1,5,1,'Episode 005: ARTS Plugin','episode-005-arts-plugin','','Kevin Clark demos his new Rails plugin, \"ARTS\":http://glu.ttono.us/articles/2006/05/29/guide-test-driven-rjs-with-arts, which allows you to test your RJS templates.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_005.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/005_arts.m4v',NULL,'<p>Kevin Clark demos his new Rails plugin, <a href=\"http://glu.ttono.us/articles/2006/05/29/guide-test-driven-rjs-with-arts\"><span class=\"caps\">ARTS</span></a>, which allows you to test your <span class=\"caps\">RJS</span> templates.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/005_arts.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_005.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-09-08 17:16:56','2006-09-08 17:16:56',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,NULL),
	(8,NULL,1,6,1,'Episode 006: Dynamic Domains','episode-006-dynamic-domains','','Chris Abad introduces the new web service, \"Outlandish\":http://out.landi.sh. He also shows us how they handle dynamic domains within Outlandish.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_006.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/006_dynamic_domains.m4v',NULL,'<p>Chris Abad introduces the new web service, <a href=\"http://out.landi.sh\">Outlandish</a>. He also shows us how they handle dynamic domains within Outlandish.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/006_dynamic_domains.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_006.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-09-08 17:20:04','2006-09-08 17:20:04',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,NULL),
	(9,NULL,1,7,1,'Episode 007: Rails Authentication','episode-007-rails-authentication','','\"Kevin Clark\":http://glu.ttono.us gives us a brief overview of two of \"Rick Olson\'s\":http://techno-weenie.net authentication plugins: \"acts_as_authenticated\":http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/acts_as_authenticated/ and \"restful_authentication\":http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/restful_authentication/.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_007.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/007_authentication.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://glu.ttono.us\">Kevin Clark</a> gives us a brief overview of two of <a href=\"http://techno-weenie.net\">Rick Olson&#8217;s</a> authentication plugins: <a href=\"http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/acts_as_authenticated/\">acts_as_authenticated</a> and <a href=\"http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/restful_authentication/\">restful_authentication</a>.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/007_authentication.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_007.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-09-08 17:24:00','2006-09-08 17:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,NULL),
	(10,NULL,2,6,1,'Episode 006: Dynamic Domains','episode-006-dynamic-domains','','\"Chris Abad\":http://blog.integralimpressions.com introduces the new web service, \"Outlandish\":http://out.landi.sh. He also shows us how they handle dynamic domains within Outlandish.\r\n\r\n\"!/images/articles/screenshot_006.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/006_dynamic_domains.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://blog.integralimpressions.com\">Chris Abad</a> introduces the new web service, <a href=\"http://out.landi.sh\">Outlandish</a>. He also shows us how they handle dynamic domains within Outlandish.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/006_dynamic_domains.m4v\"><img src=\"/images/articles/screenshot_006.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-09-08 17:20:04','2006-09-08 17:24:51','2006-09-08 17:20:17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,'Article',1,0,'2006-09-08 17:20:17'),
