	(8,NULL,1,'Episode 008: Chronic','episode-008-chronic','','\"Tom Werner\":http://www.cube6media.com/ has released the ruby gem Chronic, a natural language date and time parser. In this episode he gives us a quick run through of some of the cool points.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_008.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/008_chronic.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://www.cube6media.com/\">Tom Werner</a> has released the ruby gem Chronic, a natural language date and time parser. In this episode he gives us a quick run through of some of the cool points.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/008_chronic.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_008.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-10-03 16:30:58','2007-11-13 19:00:23','2006-10-03 16:32:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2006-10-03 16:32:29'),
	(9,NULL,1,'Episode 009: REST with Rails','episode-009-rest-with-rails','','In this episode, \"Kevin Clark\":http://glu.ttono.us shows us some of the new REST features found in Edge Rails. He covers some basic concepts such as HTTP verbs, and also takes a look at using RESTful routes.\r\n\r\nHere are the \"slides\":/pdfs/009_rest.pdf\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_009.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/009_rest.m4v',NULL,'<p>In this episode, <a href=\"http://glu.ttono.us\">Kevin Clark</a> shows us some of the new <span class=\"caps\">REST</span> features found in Edge Rails. He covers some basic concepts such as <span class=\"caps\">HTTP</span> verbs, and also takes a look at using RESTful routes.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Here are the <a href=\"/pdfs/009_rest.pdf\">slides</a></p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/009_rest.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_009.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-10-03 16:34:17','2007-11-13 19:00:19','2006-10-03 16:34:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',4,2,1,0,'2006-10-03 16:34:31'),
	(10,NULL,1,'Episode 010: REST Web Services with Rails','episode-010-rest-web-services-with-rails','','\"Chris Abad\":http://blog.integralimpressions.com talks a little bit about providing web services to your Rails application using some of the new REST features found in Edge Rails. At the end, he also throws in a bonus tip on using \"Rick Olson\'s\":http://techno-weenie.net authentication plugin \"restful_authentication\":http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/restful_authentication/ to add authentication to your REST API.\r\n\r\nHere are the \"slides\":/pdfs/010_rest_2.pdf\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_010.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/010_rest_2.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://blog.integralimpressions.com\">Chris Abad</a> talks a little bit about providing web services to your Rails application using some of the new <span class=\"caps\">REST</span> features found in Edge Rails. At the end, he also throws in a bonus tip on using <a href=\"http://techno-weenie.net\">Rick Olson&#8217;s</a> authentication plugin <a href=\"http://svn.techno-weenie.net/projects/plugins/restful_authentication/\">restful_authentication</a> to add authentication to your <span class=\"caps\">REST API</span>.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Here are the <a href=\"/pdfs/010_rest_2.pdf\">slides</a></p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/010_rest_2.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_010.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-10-03 16:37:40','2007-11-13 18:59:55','2006-10-03 16:37:55',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2006-10-03 16:37:55'),
	(11,NULL,1,'Episode 011: ActsAsTaggable Plugin','episode-011-actsastaggable-plugin','','\"Patrick Crowley\":http://mokolabs.com/ discusses his experiences with acts_as_taggable. He starts off outlining some of the differences between the \"gem\":http://rubyforge.org/projects/taggable and the \"plugin\":http://dev.rubyonrails.com/svn/rails/plugins/acts_as_taggable. Patrick then creates a simple app to show off some of the capabilities of the plugin.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_011.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/011_acts_as_taggable.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://mokolabs.com/\">Patrick Crowley</a> discusses his experiences with acts_as_taggable. He starts off outlining some of the differences between the <a href=\"http://rubyforge.org/projects/taggable\">gem</a> and the <a href=\"http://dev.rubyonrails.com/svn/rails/plugins/acts_as_taggable\">plugin</a>. Patrick then creates a simple app to show off some of the capabilities of the plugin.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/011_acts_as_taggable.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_011.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-11-06 08:31:44','2007-11-13 18:59:37','2006-11-06 08:42:37',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2006-11-06 08:42:37'),
	(12,NULL,1,'Episode 012: Deployment','episode-012-deployment','','\"Dominic Damian\":http://acorsys.com talks about the different options available to you when deploying a Rails application. He covers areas such as servers, caching, database, and hosting.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_012.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/012_deployment.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://acorsys.com\">Dominic Damian</a> talks about the different options available to you when deploying a Rails application. He covers areas such as servers, caching, database, and hosting.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/012_deployment.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_012.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2006-11-06 08:34:09','2007-11-13 18:59:17','2006-11-06 08:43:33',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2006-11-06 08:43:33'),
