	(17,NULL,1,'Episode 017: ActsNaked','episode-017-actsnaked','','In today\'s episode, \"Patrick Crowley\":http://mokolabs.com/ introduces his first Rails plugin titled ActsNaked. It\'s an easy way to \"strip your models and keep them DRY.\"\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_017.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/017_actsnaked.m4v',NULL,'<p>In today&#8217;s episode, <a href=\"http://mokolabs.com/\">Patrick Crowley</a> introduces his first Rails plugin titled ActsNaked. It&#8217;s an easy way to &#8220;strip your models and keep them <span class=\"caps\">DRY</span>.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/017_actsnaked.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_017.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2007-02-15 23:33:25','2007-11-13 18:58:53','2007-02-15 23:35:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2007-02-15 23:35:02'),
	(18,NULL,1,'Episode 018: StaffTool','episode-018-stafftool','','In this episode, \"Toby Sterrett\":http://120db.com/ gives us an update on his soon-to-be-released project StaffTool. StaffTool is a web-based church management application build with Ruby on Rails.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_018.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/018_stafftool.m4v',NULL,'<p>In this episode, <a href=\"http://120db.com/\">Toby Sterrett</a> gives us an update on his soon-to-be-released project StaffTool. StaffTool is a web-based church management application build with Ruby on Rails.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/018_stafftool.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_018.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2007-02-21 23:22:11','2007-11-13 18:58:50','2007-02-21 23:24:41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2007-02-21 23:24:41'),
	(19,NULL,1,'Episode 019: AWS S3','episode-019-aws-s3','','\"Jordan Fowler\":http://www.jordanfowler.com/ gives a presentation on Amazon\'s \"S3\":http://www.amazon.com/gp/browse.html?node=16427261 service. He also covers the \"AWS::S3\":http://amazon.rubyforge.org/ gem written by \"Marcel Molina Jr.\":http://www.vernix.org/marcel/\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_019.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/019_aws_s3.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://www.jordanfowler.com/\">Jordan Fowler</a> gives a presentation on Amazon&#8217;s <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/browse.html?node=16427261\">S3</a> service. He also covers the <a href=\"http://amazon.rubyforge.org/\"><span class=\"caps\">AWS</span>::S3</a> gem written by <a href=\"http://www.vernix.org/marcel/\">Marcel Molina Jr.</a></p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/019_aws_s3.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_019.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2007-03-03 20:29:48','2007-11-13 18:58:46','2007-03-03 20:31:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2007-03-03 20:31:05'),
	(20,NULL,1,'Episode 020: ImageScience','episode-20-imagescience','','In this episode, Tom Werner covers some of the basics of the ruby image library \"ImageScience\":http://seattlerb.rubyforge.org/ImageScience.html. ImageScience is a wrapper for the \"FreeImage\":http://sourceforge.net/projects/freeimage graphics library, and is a lightweight alternative to \"RMagick\":http://rmagick.rubyforge.org/.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_020.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/020_imagescience.mp4',NULL,'<p>In this episode, Tom Werner covers some of the basics of the ruby image library <a href=\"http://seattlerb.rubyforge.org/ImageScience.html\">ImageScience</a>. ImageScience is a wrapper for the <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/freeimage\">FreeImage</a> graphics library, and is a lightweight alternative to <a href=\"http://rmagick.rubyforge.org/\">RMagick</a>.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/020_imagescience.mp4\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_020.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2007-03-25 01:23:01','2007-11-13 18:58:22','2007-03-25 01:25:33',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',4,2,1,0,'2007-03-25 01:25:33'),
