	(22,NULL,1,'Episode 022: DRP','episode-22-drp','','\"DRP\":http://drp.rubyforge.org/ stands for Directed Ruby Programming. In this episode, Warren Henning explains exactly what that means and why you might be interested in it.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_022.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/022_drp.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://drp.rubyforge.org/\"><span class=\"caps\">DRP</span></a> stands for Directed Ruby Programming. In this episode, Warren Henning explains exactly what that means and why you might be interested in it.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/022_drp.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_022.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2007-05-31 07:03:20','2007-11-13 18:58:09','2007-05-31 07:08:50',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',4,2,1,0,'2007-05-31 07:08:50'),
	(23,NULL,1,'Episode 023: RubyInline','episode-023-rubyinline','','\"Nick Zadrozny\":http://beyondthepath.com/ shows us how to use C in Ruby with \"RubyInline\":http://www.zenspider.com/ZSS/Products/RubyInline/. As an example, Nick walks us through writing a password-generating application with the help of \"Diceware\":http://www.diceware.com/.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_023.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/023_ruby_inline.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://beyondthepath.com/\">Nick Zadrozny</a> shows us how to use C in Ruby with <a href=\"http://www.zenspider.com/ZSS/Products/RubyInline/\">RubyInline</a>. As an example, Nick walks us through writing a password-generating application with the help of <a href=\"http://www.diceware.com/\">Diceware</a>.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/023_ruby_inline.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_023.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2007-06-15 19:25:19','2007-11-13 18:58:05','2007-06-15 19:57:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2007-06-15 19:57:11'),
