	(41,NULL,2,'Episode 041: MySQL Clustering','episode-041-mysql-clustering','','\"Rob Kaufman\":http://notch8.com/ takes on database scaling with MySQL. This talk will walk you through setting up a Master (read write) Slave (read only) MySQL network, as well as a Master Master, or Multi-Master network. The talk will also cover the whys and when of database clustering.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/notch8/mysql-sm/ from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_041.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/041_mysql.m4v\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://notch8.com/\">Rob Kaufman</a> takes on database scaling with MySQL. This talk will walk you through setting up a Master (read write) Slave (read only) MySQL network, as well as a Master Master, or Multi-Master network. The talk will also cover the whys and when of database clustering.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/notch8/mysql-sm/\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/041_mysql.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_041.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-04-28 18:14:46','2008-04-28 18:18:06','2008-04-28 18:18:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-04-28 18:18:02'),
	(42,NULL,2,'Episode 042: Deploying Rails on Slicehost','episode-042-deploying-rails-on-slicehost','','\"Jared Kuolt\":http://superjared.com/ shows how to quickly deploy your Rails application to a \"Slicehost\":http://www.slicehost.com/ VPS. This talk covers installing MySQL, Nginx, Rails and Mongrel, as well as deployment using Capistrano.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://superjared.com/static/talk.pdf from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_042.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/042_slicehost.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://superjared.com/\">Jared Kuolt</a> shows how to quickly deploy your Rails application to a <a href=\"http://www.slicehost.com/\">Slicehost</a> VPS. This talk covers installing MySQL, Nginx, Rails and Mongrel, as well as deployment using Capistrano.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://superjared.com/static/talk.pdf\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/042_slicehost.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_042.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-04-28 18:29:45','2008-05-24 00:20:07','2008-04-28 18:29:54',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',7,2,1,0,'2008-04-28 18:29:54'),
	(43,NULL,2,'Episode 043: Facebook API','episode-043-facebook-api','','John Bresnik discusses the ruby library for the Facebook API, Facebooker, based on his production experience building Facebook applications. Presentation includes general overview of the Facebook API, Facebooker specifics, as well as code examples.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.rubyguerrilla.com/slides/SDRUBY-fb.pdf from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_043.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/043_facebooker.m4v\n',NULL,'<p>John Bresnik discusses the ruby library for the Facebook <span class=\"caps\">API</span>, Facebooker, based on his production experience building Facebook applications. Presentation includes general overview of the Facebook <span class=\"caps\">API</span>, Facebooker specifics, as well as code examples.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.rubyguerrilla.com/slides/SDRUBY-fb.pdf\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/043_facebooker.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_043.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-05-24 00:16:43','2008-05-24 00:30:27','2008-05-24 00:19:48',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2008-05-24 00:19:48'),
	(44,NULL,2,'Episode 044: Ext JavaScript Library','episode-044-ext-javascript-library','','Adam Grant talks about his experiences using Ext, a new Javascript library for creating advanced UI controls (like grids, trees, progress bars, etc.)\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_044.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/044_ext_javascript.m4v\n',NULL,'<p>Adam Grant talks about his experiences using Ext, a new Javascript library for creating advanced UI controls (like grids, trees, progress bars, etc.)</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/044_ext_javascript.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_044.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-05-24 00:23:01','2008-05-24 00:23:33','2008-05-24 00:23:28',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',1,2,1,0,'2008-05-24 00:23:28'),
	(45,NULL,2,'Episode 045: Merb','episode-045-merb','','Much like Rails, Merb is a MVC web-framework written in Ruby. In this talk, \"Jordan Fowler\":http://jordanfowler.com/ introduces Merb and presents some of the distinctions and tradeoffs between the two frameworks.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://docs.google.com/Present?docid=dfxf4brr_15cqs63pxf from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_045.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/045_merb.m4v\n',NULL,'<p>Much like Rails, Merb is a <span class=\"caps\">MVC</span> web-framework written in Ruby. In this talk, <a href=\"http://jordanfowler.com/\">Jordan Fowler</a> introduces Merb and presents some of the distinctions and tradeoffs between the two frameworks.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://docs.google.com/Present?docid=dfxf4brr_15cqs63pxf\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/045_merb.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_045.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-06-05 16:29:55','2008-06-13 21:31:57','2008-06-05 16:32:34',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2008-06-05 16:32:34'),
	(46,NULL,2,'Episode 046: RSpec in 15 minutes','episode-046-rspec-in-15-minutes','','\"Cliff Rhyne\":http://workingwithrails.com/person/11918-cliff-rhyne describes in 15 minutes what it takes to get up and running with RSpec.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://docs.google.com/EmbedSlideshow?docid=dd7r668z_6f5xt2tf8 from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_046.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/046_rspec.m4v\n\r\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://workingwithrails.com/person/11918-cliff-rhyne\">Cliff Rhyne</a> describes in 15 minutes what it takes to get up and running with RSpec.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://docs.google.com/EmbedSlideshow?docid=dd7r668z_6f5xt2tf8\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/046_rspec.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_046.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-06-05 16:57:12','2008-06-05 16:58:30','2008-06-05 16:57:23',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-06-05 16:57:23'),
	(47,NULL,2,'Episode 047: Lazy Indexing','episode-047-lazy-indexing','','\"Matt Aimonetti\":http://railsontherun.com/ shows how to quickly get your database queries to run faster when you are not a DBA and are running out of time.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/mattetti/lazy-indexing-466697/ from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_047.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/047_indexing.m4v\n\r\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://railsontherun.com/\">Matt Aimonetti</a> shows how to quickly get your database queries to run faster when you are not a <span class=\"caps\">DBA</span> and are running out of time.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/mattetti/lazy-indexing-466697/\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/047_indexing.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_047.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-06-13 21:24:33','2008-06-13 21:31:33','2008-06-13 21:31:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-06-13 21:31:29'),
	(48,NULL,2,'Episode 048: Ruby for Data Processing','episode-048-ruby-for-data-processing','','\"Brian Chapados\":http://chapados.org talks about using ruby & rake to build a simple workflow to coordinate external processes.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/chapados/processing-data-with-ruby from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_048.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/048_ruby_for_data.m4v\r\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://chapados.org\">Brian Chapados</a> talks about using ruby &#38; rake to build a simple workflow to coordinate external processes.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/chapados/processing-data-with-ruby\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/048_ruby_for_data.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_048.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-06-13 21:28:29','2008-06-16 23:40:11','2008-06-13 21:31:40',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-06-13 21:31:40'),
	(49,NULL,2,'Episode 049: Intro to EC2','episode-049-intro-to-ec2','','\"Chris Petersen\":http://blog.assaydepot.com gives an introduction to working with \"Amazon EC2\":http://aws.amazon.com/ec2, and discusses the advantages and disadvantage to hosting your Ruby applications there.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/cpetersen/ec2 from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_049.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/049_ec2.m4v\r\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://blog.assaydepot.com\">Chris Petersen</a> gives an introduction to working with <a href=\"http://aws.amazon.com/ec2\">Amazon <span class=\"caps\">EC2</span></a>, and discusses the advantages and disadvantage to hosting your Ruby applications there.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/cpetersen/ec2\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/049_ec2.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_049.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-06-20 00:19:11','2008-06-20 00:20:33','2008-06-20 00:19:27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-06-20 00:19:27'),
	(50,NULL,2,'Episode 050: One-man Lightning Talk','episode-050-one-man-lightning-talk','','\"Kevin Clark\":http://glu.ttono.us is back again and talking about his latest work: Rubinius, grammar parsing from ruby, kqueue, and massive build systems.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_050.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/050_kfc.m4v\r\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://glu.ttono.us\">Kevin Clark</a> is back again and talking about his latest work: Rubinius, grammar parsing from ruby, kqueue, and massive build systems.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/050_kfc.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_050.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-06-27 23:58:10','2008-06-28 00:00:49','2008-06-28 00:00:24',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-06-28 00:00:24'),
	(51,NULL,2,'Episode 051: Archaeopteryx','episode-051-archaeopteryx','','\"Giles Bowkett\":http://gilesbowkett.blogspot.com shows off his mega-cool MIDI scaffolding generator for creating dance music with Ruby. \r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_051.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/051_archaeopteryx.m4v\r\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://gilesbowkett.blogspot.com\">Giles Bowkett</a> shows off his mega-cool <span class=\"caps\">MIDI</span> scaffolding generator for creating dance music with Ruby.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/051_archaeopteryx.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_051.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-08-21 00:34:56','2008-08-30 19:49:11','2008-08-21 00:37:28',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2008-08-21 00:37:28'),
	(52,NULL,2,'Episode 052: Shadow','episode-052-shadow','','\"Jordan Fowler\":http://jordanfowler.com reveals his new \"Shadow plugin\":http://github.com/TheBreeze/shadow/tree/master/ that tracks attribute and association changes to ActiveRecord objects, making it easy to create activity feeds for your application.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_052.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/052_shadow.m4v\n',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://jordanfowler.com\">Jordan Fowler</a> reveals his new <a href=\"http://github.com/TheBreeze/shadow/tree/master/\">Shadow plugin</a> that tracks attribute and association changes to ActiveRecord objects, making it easy to create activity feeds for your application.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/052_shadow.m4v\" rel=\"enclosure\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_052.png\" alt=\"Screenshot\" /></a></p>','2008-08-21 00:44:15','2008-09-12 21:17:59','2008-08-30 19:48:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2008-08-30 19:48:45'),
	(53,NULL,2,'Episode 053: Ruby Arduino Development (RAD)','episode-053-ruby-arduino-development-rad','','Sensors and servos in hand, \"JD Barnhart\":http://jdbarnhart.com shows off the current state of \"RAD\":http://rad.rubyforge.org, the Rails inspired framework bringing convention over configuration and Ruby sensibility to the \"Arduino Physical computing platform\":http://www.arduino.cc.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/madrona/rad-demo-at-sd-ruby-presentation/ from this talk. \r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_053.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/053_rad.m4v',NULL,'<p>Sensors and servos in hand, <a href=\"http://jdbarnhart.com\">JD Barnhart</a> shows off the current state of <a href=\"http://rad.rubyforge.org\"><span class=\"caps\">RAD</span></a>, the Rails inspired framework bringing convention over configuration and Ruby sensibility to the <a href=\"http://www.arduino.cc\">Arduino Physical computing platform</a>.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/madrona/rad-demo-at-sd-ruby-presentation/\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/053_rad.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_053.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-08-22 18:36:10','2008-09-20 15:31:19','2008-09-12 21:17:43',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',3,2,1,0,'2008-09-12 21:17:43'),
	(54,NULL,2,'Episode 054: Paperclip','episode-054-paperclip','','\"Patrick Crowley\":http://the.railsi.st talks about \"Paperclip\":http://www.thoughtbot.com/projects/paperclip, a lightweight plugin for handling attachments.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/mokolabs/paperclip-presentation/ from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_054.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/054_paperclip.m4v',NULL,'<p><a href=\"http://the.railsi.st\">Patrick Crowley</a> talks about <a href=\"http://www.thoughtbot.com/projects/paperclip\">Paperclip</a>, a lightweight plugin for handling attachments.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/mokolabs/paperclip-presentation/\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/054_paperclip.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_054.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-08-22 18:36:47','2008-10-10 15:05:10','2008-09-20 15:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',2,2,1,0,'2008-09-20 15:31:00'),
	(55,NULL,2,'Episode 055: MySQL, Postgres, and Rails','episode-055-postgres','','Guyren Howe has considerable experience with both \"MySQL\":http://mysql.com and \"PostgreSQL\":http://www.postgresql.org/. He discusses the myriad technical and other advantages to using PostgreSQL instead of MySQL for, well, pretty much anything.\r\n\r\nBonus content: \"download the slides\":http://www.slideshare.net/gisborne/postgres-presentation-presentation/ from this talk.\r\n\r\n\"!http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_055.png!\":http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/055_postgres.m4v\r\n',NULL,'<p>Guyren Howe has considerable experience with both <a href=\"http://mysql.com\">MySQL</a> and <a href=\"http://www.postgresql.org/\">PostgreSQL</a>. He discusses the myriad technical and other advantages to using PostgreSQL instead of MySQL for, well, pretty much anything.</p>\n\n\n	<p>Bonus content: <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/gisborne/postgres-presentation-presentation/\">download the slides</a> from this talk.</p>\n\n\n	<p><a href=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/podcasts/055_postgres.m4v\"><img src=\"http://podcast.sdruby.com/images/articles/screenshot_055.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','2008-08-22 18:37:32','2008-10-10 15:07:37','2008-10-10 15:04:53',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'--- \n- :textile_filter\n',4,2,1,0,'2008-10-10 15:04:53');
